Empirical bayesan analysis

Source: R/differential_expression.R
calculate_EB.Rd

Function which uses a model matrix to calculate the empirical Bayesian results from a provided microarray normalized and corrected Elist.

calculate_EB(micro_arr_dta, matrix_model, comparison)

Arguments

micro_arr_dta

An Elist object containing the normalized and corrected microarray data

matrix_model

the matrix model as created by the prep_matrix()

comparison

The name of the comparison being run

Value

The empirical Bayesian results
